<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

<worksheet xml:id="dc1-reading" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>DC-1 Reading</title>
    <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li><p>Things you should understand and know:
        <ul>
            <li>The various notations for partial derivatives</li>
            <li>The meaning of a partial differential equation</li>
            <li>When a function of two variables is differentiable</li>
        </ul></p>
        <p>Things you should be able to do:
        <ul>
            <li>Calculate a partial derivative of a function of two or more variables</li>
            <li>Find higher-order partial derivatives of functions of two or more variables</li>
        </ul></p>
      </li>
      <li><p>You will be assessed on the following criteria:
        <ul>
          <li><p>Problem structure: Solution should be organized and easy to follow, with clear, complete steps 
              that follow progressively from one to the next.</p></li>
          <li><p>Partial Derivatives: Understand the concept of partial derivatives and their applications. Evaluate 
            first-order and higher order partial derivatives of functions of several variables.</p></li>
          <li><p>Evaluate partial derivatives at specific points and interpret their meaning.</p></li>
        </ul></p>
      </li>
    </ul>
    </objectives>
        <p>All of the readings for this course come from the OpenStax Calculus 
            Volume 3 textbook, which is available for free online at 
            <url href="https://openstax.org/details/books/calculus-volume-3">
                https://openstax.org/details/books/calculus-volume-3</url>. You 
                can read the textbook online or download a PDF version. 
                The textbook is also available in print from various retailers 
                if you prefer a physical copy.</p>
        <p>For this lesson, you should read sections <url href="https://openstax.org/books/calculus-volume-3/pages/4-3-partial-derivatives">
            4.3 Partial Derivatives</url>. You should read through the sections carefully, 
            making sure to understand the definitions, examples, and key ideas. 
            You should also work through the exercises at the end of each section 
            to test your understanding and practice applying the concepts. Some of the 
            exercises at the end of the section are assigned in the WP assignments.</p>      
</worksheet>
